1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,470
Production incidents force small teams to assemble evidence, diagnose risk,
and coordinate a safe fix. Incident Commander AI makes that work auditable.

2
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:31,440
The verified local demo starts with simulated checkout telemetry. Evidence gets
stable provenance, and secret-shaped values are redacted before investigation.

3
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:55,940
The investigation correlates deployment, stack trace, and commit evidence.
Every claim is cited. A human must approve the bounded two-file plan.

4
00:00:55,940 --> 00:01:24,570
An explicitly simulated fixture code agent works in an isolated workspace.
Deterministic tests, type checks, risk review, and a second approval follow.

5
00:01:24,570 --> 00:01:47,470
The local result is RESOLUTION_DRAFTED: two approvals, a simulated draft-PR
artifact, audience-specific updates, and an evidence-linked postmortem.

6
00:01:47,470 --> 00:02:12,410
The fixture workflow is backed by tests, browser automation, repeated demo
runs, and a secret scan. A separate GPT-5.6 structured-output smoke test passed.

